OL,6,FHer elderly father, Willy Leeson, and
OL,7,Fbrother, Neville, sat with her son,
OL,8,FBen, were in court as the judgment was
OL,9,Fgiven.
OL,11,FThey run a successful skip and plant
OL,12,Fhire business in south Manchester,
OL,13,Fwhich Ms Leeson helped to run, and
OL,14,Fwhere she first came into contact with
OL,15,FMcPherson, who claimed to be a
OL,16,Fsuccessful property developer.
OL,18,FMcPherson had taken out multiple
OL,19,Fsecret life insurance policies on his
OL,20,Fwife before her death, worth #3.5
OL,21,Fmillion alone.
